<!--MOVEMENT ORDERS TABLES GO HERE-->
	<table border=0 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	<tr><td class=bodycopy>

This is a simple traditional variant of Diplomacy, involving the
usual seven powers. There are only seven spaces on the board -- each
of these is the single home supply center for one of the powers.
Every one of the seven spaces is connected to every other space by land.
To begin the game, each player begins with one army in his home supply
center.
<P>
The object of the game is to accumulate four supply centers.

		<!--BODYCOPY ENDS HERE-->
	</td>
